It's 30% more brighter and sharper than comparable 4’’ 720p native projectors on the market, providing you with probably the best home cinema experience.

Wireless Screen Mirroring in Simple Steps-For iOS device: 1. Turn on projector and choose “Set up”; 2. Choose network and set up Wi-Fi password to connect the projector to a Wi-Fi router; 3. Open “iOS Screen” on the projector, connect your iOS device to the same Wi-Fi router; 4. Turn on screen mirroring on your iOS device to search projector device “DBPOWER-XXXX” and connect it. Wireless Screen Mirroring in Simple Steps-For Android device: 1. Open “Android Screen” on the projector; 2. Turn on WLAN and enter “Setting”on your Android device; 3. Turn on “Smart View” on your Android device; 4. Search projector device “DBPOWER-XXXX” and connect it .

Wired Screen Mirroring in Simple Steps-For iOS device: 1. Turn on projector and choose “iOS Screen”; 2. Connect your iOS device with projector’s USB port via your iOS phone USB cable; 3. Click “Trust” then put your lock screen password; 4. Then the screen mirroring will start. Wired Screen Mirroring in Simple Steps-For Android device: 1. Turn on projector and choose “Android Screen”; 2. Connect your Android device with projector’s OUTPUT 5V port via your Android phone USB cable; 3. Open the USB debugging; 4. Then the screen mirroring will start.

Upgrade 9000Lux High Brightness , Full HD Visual Performance Adopting 2022 latest Led light technology projects a clear image 9000Lux (Over 200 ANSI), 4.3'' lcd screen of our native 720p wifi projector makes it 30% more brighter and sharper than comparable 4’’ 720p native projectors on the market, providing you with probably the best home cinema experience. Also this technology saves your eyes while still allowing you to enjoy movies, sports, TV. 3500:1 High Contrast The video projector with a high contrast ratio allows to enjoying clearly shadow detail and deep black levels, adding a sense of depth and dimension to the picture which presents you a real, dynamic and color vibrant projection image quality. Multi Projector Mode You could flip the image in the settings. It can support front projection and back projection. It is recommended for those who want to save more space to mount it on the ceiling.

Warm Tips: 1. Ideal for use in low-light environments. Do not recommend for PPT, Word, Excel or business presentations. 2. Due to HDCP copyright, this wireless projection doesn't support Netflix, Amazon Prime and Hulu, but you could use play these videos via HDMI connection such as amazon fire stick. 3. Due to Netflix copyright protection issue, the sound of some Netfilx videos may not work properly, please turn off the Dolby Sound to make the sound work properly.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 17, 2022
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. This is my second projector for this company. I primarily use them for Halloween. I decided to set it up for a movie night in the yard. Picture quality is phenomenal. Speakers are OK, but I use an exterior system that I plug into the aux port. The screen mirror function works fine on my Galaxy. I just plug my Roku into the HDMI port, and everything works exactly as it does on my TV. For the small price, you get alot more than what you pay for.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 13, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Does what I want and does it well
reviews.reviewText: I wanted something that was bright enough to show movies outside before it was completely dark. This does that. It also has lighted buttons (very helpful) and can be mounted on a tripod. The built-in speakers are surprisingly load and clear for our needs. If more volume is needed , external speakers such as a soundbar can be connected to the headphone jack The carrying case keeps the projector protected and the cables from getting lost. Menus are clear and easy to navigate. It connected to my WiFi without issues. Only negative was choppy audio when streaming from my android phone. I'm not worried about that, because I plan on using a DVD player anyway. I would love it if I could connect a soundbar via bluetooth. Bottom line. It does what I bought it for, and does it well. Good value for the money.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Easy to set up
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I originally ordered a different projector. I had issues straight out of the box. Once returned, I stumbled onto this one. The ease of setting this one up was very impressive. It found and connected to my home wifi immediately. The clarity of the picture is also impressive. That image in my video is from 11ish in the am. So it was kind of bright and you could see it clear as day. The carrying case is also nice. Very clear instructions as well.
